THE NAME OF THE GAME 
This 1968-1971 series had three rotating stars, who were featured in independent episodes tied together by a loose common theme. The commonality was Howard Publications, the self-made publishing empire of Glenn Howard (Gene Barry). Episodes featuring Howard focused on his business and political confrontations and his flamboyant lifestyle. Other episodes featured Jeff Dillon (Anthony Franciosa), a crusading investigative reporter, or Dan Farrell (Robert Stack). Farrell was a retired FBI agent who used his position as the editor of "Crime Magazine" to wage a literary war against organized crime. Common to all three elements was Peggy Maxwell (Susan Saint James), the bright, ambitious and occasionally kooky editorial assistant to all three men.

1. The Fear Of High Places    9/20/1968
